register.description:
Last Measured Battery Voltage
This register should be read when BATUPD.STA = 1

bitfield.description: Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.

Integer part:
0x0: Battery voltage = 0V + fractional part ... 0x3: Battery voltage = 3V + fractional part 0x4: Battery voltage = 4V + fractional part
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.

bitenum.description: New battery voltage present

bitenum.description: No update since last clear

register.description:
Last measured Temperature in Degree Celsius
This register should be read when TEMPUPD.STA = 1.

bitfield.description: Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.

Integer part of temperature value (signed) Total value = INT + FRAC 2's complement encoding
0x100: Min value (-256°C) 0x1D8: -40°C 0x1FF: -1°C 0x00: 0°C 0x1B: 27°C 0x55: 85°C 0xFF: Max value (255°C)
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.

bitfield.description: Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.

DCDC load meter high threshold value for adaptive IPEAK adjustment. DCDC load meter output is in percentage scale so the applicable values are 'd1 to 'd100. Values from 'd101 to 'd127 are invalid and not to be used.
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.

DCDC load meter low threshold value for adaptive IPEAK adjustment. DCDC load meter output is in percentage scale so the applicable values are 'd1 to 'd100. Values from 'd101 to 'd127 are invalid and not to be used.
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.

This bit is used to enable adaptive IPEAK adjustment scheme in hardware. When this bit is set, DCDC IPEAK value is automatically adjusted to suitable value by sensing the DCDC load meter output for better DCDC operational efficiency.
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.
This bit is used to enable DCDC load meter. Software can obtain DCDC load meter value from DCDCSTAT regiser and adjust IPEAK setting in SYS0.TDCDC register accordingly.
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.

DCDC IPEAK value. This value is same as what is programmed in SYS0:TMUTE4.IPEAK when adaptive IPEAK adjustment scheme is not enabled, and it shows current IPEAK value applied by hardware when adaptive IPEAK adjustment scheme is enabled. Note: Software can only support IPEAK = 1
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.
This indicates DCDC load meter output value in percentage scale. Applicable range is 'd1 to 'd100.
